Nicky Ioannou (born 3 July 1987) is a football full back who played in the Football League for Barnet.
Ioannou began his career in Charlton Athletic's academy and completed an apprenticeship with Rushden & Diamonds, during which he played for Cyprus U19, before joining Barnet in 2006. He spent time on loan to Welwyn Garden City in 2007 before making his Football League debut against Bristol Rovers on 14 April 2007. He was playing for Welwyn in 2010.
